    <mj-preview> SafetyDriven
KEEPS YOU
ROLLING SAFELY
DURING THE
PANDEMIC&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</mj-preview>
  </mj-head>
  <mj-body background-color="#fff">
    <mj-section padding="0px" background-color="#fff">
      <mj-column background-color="#fff" padding="0px" width="60%">
        <mj-image padding="0px" src="https://www.trucknews.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/header1.jpg" width="391px" href="https://safetydriven.ca/covid-19/" />
        <mj-image padding="0px" src="https://www.trucknews.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/header2.jpg" href="https://safetydriven.ca/covid-19/" />
      </mj-column>
      <mj-column background-color="#fff" padding="0px" width="39%">
        <mj-image padding="0px" src="https://www.trucknews.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/header4.jpg" width="251px" href="https://www.cmeexpo.ca" />
        <mj-text color="#000" font-size="14px" font-weight="700" padding-bottom="0px" align="left">WE PARTNER WITH YOU TO BUILD YOUR SAFETY PROGRAM</mj-text>
        <mj-text color="#000" font-size="12px" font-weight="400" padding-bottom="0px" align="left">If the COVID-19 pandemic has taught the world anything, it is that we cannot exist without trucking. <a href="https://safetydriven.ca/" style="color:#f26522">SafetyDriven-Trucking Safety Council of BC</a> provides free health and safety program development, training, and resources to the general trucking
          and moving and storage industries and during the coronavirus outbreak, we still have your back. </mj-text>
        <mj-text color="#000" font-size="12px" font-weight="400" padding-bottom="0px" align="left">With more than 3 million confirmed cases worldwide, precautions are necessary and may continue for some time. Every player involved with trucking and moving and storage needs reliable <a href="https://safetydriven.ca/resource/information-procedures-and-guidance/" style="color:#f26522">information</a> and clearly defined protocols. SafetyDriven is
          helping you <a href="https://safetydriven.ca/resource/managing-a-pandemic-on-site/" style="color:#f26522"> manage the pandemic </a> by providing a new series of free industry-specific resources about <a href="https://safetydriven.ca/covid-19/" style="color:#f26522">COVID-19</a> to keep you on the move and keep your personnel safe. </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>


    <mj-section padding="20px" background-color="#fff">
     <mj-column background-color="#fff" padding="5px" padding-bottom="0px" width="25%">
        <mj-text color="#f26522" font-size="15px" font-weight="700" padding="0px" align="left">Be Resourceful</mj-text>
       <mj-text color="#000" font-size="12px" font-weight="400" padding="0px" padding-top="5px" align="left">Visit <a href="https://safetydriven.ca/covid-19/" style="color:#f26522;">safetydriven.ca/covid-19/</a> to
download information sheets, forms
to customize for your business, and
tools to help you ensure employee
and client safety. The material,
available as Word documents or
PDFs, is directed toward drivers
and workers, health and safety
representatives, and managers and
supervisors. As well, we’re linking you
         to <a href="https://safetydriven.ca/covid-19/" style="color:#f26522">resources from the experts</a>, such
as WorkSafeBC, the World Health
Organization, and the BC Centre for
Disease Control.  </mj-text>

      </mj-column>
      <mj-column background-color="#fff" padding="5px" padding-bottom="0px" width="25%">
        <mj-text color="#f26522" font-size="15px" font-weight="700" padding="0px" align="left">Stay Ready</mj-text>
  <mj-text color="#000" font-size="12px" font-weight="400" padding="0px" padding-top="5px" align="left">You can address your employees’
concerns by applying SafetyDriven’s
    <a href="https://safetydriven.ca/type_resources/safe-work-procedures/" style="color:#f26522">Safe Work Procedures</a> for COVID-19,
    including an <a href="https://safetydriven.ca/resource/exposure-control-plan-word/" style="color:#f26522">exposure control plan</a>
    and <a href="https://safetydriven.ca/resource/working-alone-in-isolation/" style="color:#f26522">guidelines</a> for working alone or
in isolation. Useful tools to ensure
safety on-site include the <a href="https://safetydriven.ca/resource/visitor-self-assessment-questionnaire/" style="color:#f26522">Health
    Screening Tool</a> and the <a href="https://safetydriven.ca/resource/visitor-self-assessment-questionnaire/" style="color:#f26522">Visitor
    Self-Assessment Questionnaire</a>.
Should the worst happen, and
you suspect a case of COVID-19
on-site, refer to our procedures for a
    <a href="https://safetydriven.ca/resource/procedures-for-presumed-case-on-site/" style="color:#f26522">presumptive case</a>. </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
      <mj-column background-color="#fff" padding="5px" padding-bottom="0px" width="25%">
         <mj-text color="#f26522" font-size="15px" font-weight="700" padding="0px" align="left">Stay Informed</mj-text>
  <mj-text color="#000" font-size="12px" font-weight="400" padding="0px" padding-top="5px" align="left">One of the best things you can do
right now is communicate clearly
with your staff, vendors, and clients,
including reassuring customers, in
writing, that your <a href="https://safetydriven.ca/resource/it-is-safe-to-work-with-our-drivers-letter/" style="color:#f26522">drivers are safe to
    work with</a>. Among our <a href="https://safetydriven.ca/type_resources/templates-forms/" style="color:#f26522">templates
    and forms</a> you will find a range of
ways to help you keep the lines of
communication open and provide
explicit information for having have
    <a href="https://safetydriven.ca/resource/what-i-will-do-for-you-procedure/" style="color:#f26522">drivers on-site safely</a>, emphasizing
that safety is a two-way street—you
    <a href="https://safetydriven.ca/resource/what-you-can-do-for-our-driver-checklist-pdf/" style="color:#f26522">expect clients</a> to help your drivers
and workers operate safely for your
mutual benefit.  </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
      <mj-column background-color="#fff" padding="5px" padding-bottom="0px" width="25%">
        <mj-text color="#f26522" font-size="15px" font-weight="700" padding="0px" align="left">Stay Updated</mj-text>
  <mj-text color="#000" font-size="12px" font-weight="400" padding="0px" padding-top="5px" align="left">Despite the seriousness of COVID-19, some
aspects of business cannot be ignored,
including maintaining your Certificate of
Recognition (COR) program, workplace
hygiene, and getting paid. SafetyDriven’s
COR Team will continue to provide
information and updates, including the
    <a href="https://safetydriven.ca/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/RES_Hnd_na_COR_COVID-19-COR-Program-Update_FINALApril2020.pdf" style="color:#f26522">BC COR Program Update</a>. The pandemic
    requires  <a href="https://safetydriven.ca/resource/enhanced-surface-cleaning-and-disinfecting/" style="color:#f26522">enhanced hygiene protocols</a>, and
    we spell it out in our  <a href="https://safetydriven.ca/type_resources/safety-handouts/" style="color:#f26522">Safety Handouts</a>, which
    include a useful  <a href="https://safetydriven.ca/resource/coronavirus-covid-19-faq-punjabi/" style="color:#f26522">coronavirus FAQ</a> in Punjabi.
Clients and drivers will surely have questions
about handling cash and documents;
guide and reassure them with a <a href="https://safetydriven.ca/resource/handling-documents-and-cash-process/" style="color:#f26522">process for
    handling documents and cash.</a> </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
